H3651  
כּן  
כֵּן ‎ kên  
*kane*  
From [3559](h3559.md) properly *set* upright; hence (figuratively as
adjective) *just*; but usually (as adverb or conjugation) *rightly* or
*so* (in various applications to manner, time and relation; often with
other particles): - + after that (this, -ward, -wards), as . . . as, +
\[for-\] asmuch as yet, + be (for which) cause, + following, howbeit, in
(the) like (manner, -wise), X the more, right, (even) so, state,
straightway, such (thing), surely, + there (where) -fore, this, thus,
true, well, X you.  
